<br>
I cried all the way back to the house, and all the way to work, just hating my life and how it had turned out, and hating my ex, and hating myself for taking it out on the sweetest little 2nd grader you ever knew. He is the light of my life, the reason I get out of bed and drag myself through another day, and as hard as it all is, he is worth it. <br>
<br>
The hardest part of being a single parent, especially with a young child, is the total aloneness... there is no one to celebrate your birthday, or hold you and hug you when you've had a bad day and your child(ren) are driving you nuts, no one to say &quot;Here, you go take a hot bath... take as long as you like. I have things under control out here.&quot;<br>
<br>
I was really feeling alone and worn out this morning... and this post made a world of difference. I can't thank you enough.<br>
<br>
poFaeli<br>
